Package: smartpkg
Title: Smart R Package Installer with Automatic Fastest Mirror Selection
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Yang", family = "Leng", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "yang.leng815@gmail.com")
Description: Provides smart_install(), a unified installer for R packages from
    CRAN, Bioconductor, GitHub, and local archives. It detects package sources,
    selects responsive CRAN and Bioconductor mirrors, filters Bioconductor
    mirrors by release compatibility, caches mirror choices, and dispatches to
    install.packages(), BiocManager::install(), or remotes::install_github() as
    appropriate.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    tools,
    utils
Suggests:
    curl,
    BiocManager,
    remotes,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
NeedsCompilation: no
